  "time_ut": 1656829317,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dba\u0dbd \u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dba\u0dda \u0db6\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb \u0dc0\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0ddd\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0dbb\u0dd4. 150\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Eggs in the spring season cost Rs. 150",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Minister of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation, Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera, has instructed the Department of Agriculture to buy egg rice grown in the yala season at 150 rupees per kilo.",
        "Currently, the price set by the Department of Agriculture for a kilo of eggs and rice is 140 rupees, but since that price is not a fair price for them from the point of view of the farmers, the price should be raised to 150 rupees, and a ministerial paper will be prepared to get the approval of the cabinet in this regard. The minister further advised.",
        "Preparation of egg rice required for cultivation in the 2022 high season will be done by purchasing rice harvests from farmers who have grown egg rice in the early season. As it is necessary for the quality of egg rice to be processed, officials of the Department of Agriculture have been deployed to check the egg rice harvest.",
        "The quantity of egg rice required for the 2022/23 season is 40 lakh bushels. The amount of egg rice obtained by the government egg rice farms is between 10-12 percent of the total requirement. The remaining eggs are procured from rice farmers.",
        "The Minister of Agriculture states that he has received information that some farmers who cultivated egg rice are selling their harvest to traders at a higher price for processing rice. Also not to sell egg rice to traders to prepare rice for consumption.",
        "The Minister also said that the Department of Agriculture should immediately intervene to buy the egg rice owned by the farmers as there is a possibility of a shortage of egg rice in the next season.",
        "Meanwhile, the Paddy Marketing Board has made arrangements to purchase more paddy crops in the new season. A Cabinet paper has been prepared to get the approval of the Cabinet for that."
      ],
